Stage 1: Named Entity Recognition¶

Finding the main characters¶

It is noted without processing the text that Amyas Leigh is the main character of the book. However, the NER process allows the recognition of other prominent characters. The identified named_entities are counted to find the first and second most mentioned charcater, whom will be also considered a main character.

Stage 2: Preprocessing - Extracting Sentences Associated to Characters¶

Setup: Data Cleaning Functions for Sentences¶

In [ ]:
# function to expand contraction
def expand_contraction(text):
      expanded_text = []   
      for word in text.split():
            expanded_text.append(contractions.fix(word))
      expanded_text = ' '.join(expanded_text)  
      return expanded_text

# function to remove special characters
def remove_special_characters(text, remove_digits=False):
    pattern = r'[^a-zA-z0-9\s]' if not remove_digits else r'[^a-zA-z\s]'
    text = re.sub(pattern, '', text)
    return text

# function integrating all preprocess functions
def preprocess(sent, stop_words = spacy.lang.en.stop_words.STOP_WORDS):
    clean_sent = " ".join([token.lemma_ for token in sent if token not in stop_words]) # lemmatisation and remove stop words
    clean_sent = re.sub(r'[\r|\n|\r\n]+', '\n', clean_sent) # strip html tags
    clean_sent = clean_sent.lower() # all lowercase for sentence
    clean_sent = unidecode(clean_sent) # remove accented characters
    clean_sent = expand_contraction(clean_sent) # expand contraction
    clean_sent = remove_special_characters(clean_sent) # remove special characters 
    return clean_sent

Extract sentences associated to Amyas Leigh and Frank Leigh respectively¶

In [ ]:
# extract the sentences for Amyas and Frank respectively
Amyas_name_alias = []
Amyas_sentences = []
Frank_name_alias = []
Frank_sentences = []


sentences = [sent for sent in doc.sents]
for sent in sentences:
    str_sent = " ".join([word.text for word in sent])
    nlp_sent = nlp(str_sent)
    for ent in nlp_sent.ents:
        if ent.text in Amyas_names:
            Amyas_name_alias.append(ent.text)
            Amyas_sentences.append(preprocess(sent))
            break
        if ent.text in Frank_names:
            Frank_name_alias.append(ent.text)
            Frank_sentences.append(preprocess(sent))
            break

Stage 3 - Sentimental Analysis Using Vader¶

Setup¶

In [ ]:
# setup
from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer
sid = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()
In [ ]:
# function to finding mood words
def find_mood_words(df, comp_label):
    mood_words = []
    if comp_label == 'pos': 
        for sent in df[df['comp_label']==comp_label]['sentence']: # select all sentences with positive comp_label and iterate
            for i in [word for word in (sent.split())]: # split the sentences word by word to find the polarity score of each word
                if sid.polarity_scores(i)['compound'] >= 0.5: # extact the word if the word has positive compound score (>=0.5)
                    mood_words.append(i)                

    if comp_label == 'neg':
        for sent in df[df['comp_label']==comp_label]['sentence']: # select all sentences with negative comp_label and iterate
            for i in [word for word in (sent.split())]: # split the sentences word by word to find the polarity score of each word
                if sid.polarity_scores(i)['compound'] <= -0.5:  # extact the word if the word has negative compound score (<= -0.5)
                    mood_words.append(i)
                    
    return mood_words

# function for plotting the moodwords in wordcloud
def plot_wordcloud(mood_words,output_filename='mood_words'):
    wordcloud = WordCloud().generate(' '.join(mood_words))
    #wordcloud.to_file(output_filename + '.png')    # save the image if needed
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")

Stage 3A: Analysis on Amyas Leigh¶

In [ ]:
# Obtain compound score from Vader and save to new column 'compound'
# Create new column 'compund label' by calculating the compound scores, 'pos' if >=0.5, 'neu' if <0.5 and > -0.5, 'neg' if <=-0.5 
Amyas_df['compound'] = Amyas_df['sentence'].apply(lambda content: sid.polarity_scores(content)['compound'])
Amyas_df['comp_label'] = Amyas_df['compound'].apply(lambda c: 'pos' if c >=0.5 else ('neg' if c<=-0.5 else 'neu'))

Stage 4A: Result of sentiment analysis on Amyas Leigh¶

In [ ]:
# Generating a pie chart to visualise the result of sentiment analysis on Amyas
def percentage(part, whole):
    return 100 * float(part)/float(whole)

negative = percentage(sum(Amyas_df['comp_label']=='neg'), len(Amyas_df['comp_label']))
neutral = percentage(sum(Amyas_df['comp_label']=='neu'), len(Amyas_df['comp_label']))
positive = percentage(sum(Amyas_df['comp_label']=='pos'), len(Amyas_df['comp_label']))

positive = format(positive, '.2f')
neutral = format(neutral, '.2f')
negative = format(negative, '.2f')

labels = ['Positive ['+str(positive)+'%]',
          'Neutral ['+str(neutral)+'%]',
          'Negative ['+str(negative)+'%]']

sizes = [positive, neutral, negative]
colors = ['yellowgreen', 'gold', 'red']

patches, text = plt.pie(sizes, colors = colors, startangle = 90)

plt.legend(patches, labels, loc = "best")
plt.title('Sentiment Analysis on Amyas Leigh in Westward Ho!')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
